decks.notes: The main concept of this deck is to generate a large amount of mana and use it to cast Paradoxical Outcome, which allows the player to return a number of nonland permanents they control to their hand and draw that many cards. With cards like Tolarian Academy, Mishra's Workshop, and Grim Monolith, the deck can generate a lot of mana quickly. By bouncing and drawing cards with Paradoxical Outcome, the player can create a storm-like effect, casting multiple spells in a single turn and overwhelming the opponent. The deck also utilizes artifacts and artifact tutors like Tinker and Karn, the Great Creator for additional advantage and disruption.

The key concept of this deck is to control the game through counterspells and removal, utilizing the power of blue and white cards. The deck aims to establish a strong board presence by using cards like Lavinia, Azorius Renegade, and Mishra's Bauble to disrupt opponents' strategies. It also takes advantage of card advantage with spells like Ancestral Recall, Dig Through Time, and Treasure Cruise. The deck includes various ways to protect its own spells and permanents through cards like Force of Will and Lórien Revealed. It aims to maintain control of the game until it can secure a victory.
